main event: Six unidentified objects with the appearance of upside down light colored cones were sighted in Cashmere, Washington on 30 September 1957.
interesting points: The objects were traveling very fast and appeared to drop from an altitude,The objects appeared and disappeared while in view,The sighting was reported by at least 4 adults and 8-12 children,The observing conditions were clear with high cirrus clouds,The investigating officer initially laughed at the report, causing indignation among the witnesses.
sighted object: six unidentified objects resembling upside down light colored cones
